first_reading.text:
[[Is 1,10]]Hear the word of the LORD, princes of Sodom! Listen to the instruction of our God, people of Gomorrah!
[[Is 1,16]]Wash yourselves clean! Put away your misdeeds from before my eyes; cease doing evil;
[[Is 1,17]]learn to do good. Make justice your aim: redress the wronged, hear the orphan's plea, defend the widow.
[[Is 1,18]]Come now, let us set things right, says the LORD: Though your sins be like scarlet, they may become white as snow; Though they be crimson red, they may become white as wool.
[[Is 1,19]]If you are willing, and obey, you shall eat the good things of the land;
[[Is 1,20]]But if you refuse and resist, the sword shall consume you: for the mouth of the LORD has spoken!
